      "description": "The audit flags `plugins/discovery.rs::project_overrides_global` for mutating `HOME` without `#[serial]`, which can flake under parallel tests and makes the SAFETY comment inaccurate. Add `#[serial]` (or remove the env mutation) so the test matches its isolation claims. Outcome: stable parallel test runs and accurate safety documentation for that test.\n\nValidation: In `crates/ralph/src/plugins/discovery.rs`, `project_overrides_global` (around lines 146–187) uses `unsafe { std::env::set_var(\"HOME\", ...) }` and documents single-threaded assumptions, but the test module is not `#[serial]`. The test body currently ends after restoring `HOME` and performs no assertions on `discover_plugins`, so fixing isolation may pair naturally with completing the intended override assertion.",
