      "id": "RQ-0015",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Keep run-one queue lock alive through execution",
      "description": "Principles violated: E) Make bugs hard to write, H) Operational hygiene, J) Consistency/Integrity. The direct run-one path acquires a queue lock in prepare_run_one_context, but the guard is a local variable and is dropped before task selection, mark_task_doing, runner execution, and completion bookkeeping. That creates a race window where another Ralph process can mutate the same queue while run-one believes it is protected. Minimal fix: make RunOneContext own the lock guard for QueueLockMode::Acquire and hold it through queue-mutating completion while preserving QueueLockMode::Held for callers that already hold the lock.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "concurrency",
        "queue",
        "runner"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_one/context.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_one/orchestration.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_one/execution_setup.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/context.rs"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_one/context.rs:52 :: prepare_run_one_context stores the acquired queue lock in a local _queue_lock guard.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_one/orchestration.rs:45 :: RunOneContext has resolved/config/agent fields but no lock guard field, so the lock cannot outlive context preparation.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_one/orchestration.rs:161 :: task selection happens after prepare_run_one_context returns.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_one/execution_setup.rs:122 :: execution setup calls mark_task_doing after selection.",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/context.rs:50 :: mark_task_doing reloads and saves the queue file.",
        "workflow: rg -n \"let _queue_lock|struct RunOneContext|mark_task_doing\\(|queue::save_queue\\(&resolved.queue_path\" crates/ralph/src/commands/run/run_one crates/ralph/src/commands/run/context.rs -g '*.rs' :: showed lock acquisition, missing context field, and later queue mutation."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Add an owned Option queue-lock guard field to RunOneContext or an equivalent lifetime holder.",
        "Populate it only when QueueLockMode::Acquire is used; keep Held mode lock-free to avoid deadlocks in loop or machine surfaces that already hold a lock.",
        "Add a regression test that attempts to acquire the queue lock while run-one is between context preparation and execution setup and proves it remains blocked.",
        "Verify by running the focused run-one queue-lock tests plus make check-env-safety format-check type-check lint test."
      ],
      "notes": [
        "RunOneContext now owns acquired queue locks for the run-one critical section.",
