      "id": "RQ-0039",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Prefer MachineErrorDocument in RalphMac machine command failures",
      "description": "Several RalphMac machine-command helpers still surface raw stderr text when a subprocess fails, which means users can see opaque JSON when the CLI emits the documented `machine_error` payload on stderr. `Workspace+Decompose` and queue recovery helpers currently stringify stderr directly, while task mutation conflict handling already decodes `MachineErrorDocument` for structured classification. Acceptance criteria: RalphCore centralizes machine-command failure decoding so decompose, queue recovery helpers, and other `runAndCollect` machine-command paths prefer `MachineErrorDocument` fields (`code`, `message`, optional `detail`, `retryable`) when present, with tests and behavior aligned to `docs/machine-contract.md`.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "macos",
        "machine-contract",
        "ux",
        "error-handling"
      ],
      "scope": [
