        "apps/RalphMac/RalphCoreTests",
        "docs/machine-contract.md",
        "make agent-ci"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "user-request: Cross-surface coherence (RalphMac error handling): Several machine subprocess helpers (e.g. Workspace+Decompose runTaskDecompose) surface raw stderr on failure, while Workspace+TaskMutations already decodes MachineErrorDocument from stderr for classification (taskConflict).",
        "path: docs/machine-contract.md:39 :: `machine_error` is the versioned machine stderr contract for failed `ralph machine ...` commands.",
        "path: docs/machine-contract.md:49 :: machine clients should decode the structured error document instead of scraping English stderr text.",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/ConfigModels.swift:187 :: RalphMac already defines `MachineErrorDocument` and a decode helper.",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/Workspace+Decompose.swift:78 :: failed `machine task decompose` calls currently throw `collected.stderr` directly.",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/Workspace+ErrorRecovery.swift:136 :: queue recovery helpers currently throw raw stderr for failed machine-command subprocesses.",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/Workspace+TaskMutations.swift:261 :: task mutation conflict handling already decodes `MachineErrorDocument` from stderr for classification.",
        "path: apps/RalphMac/RalphCore/RalphCLIClient+Retry.swift:60 :: collected machine command output already exposes a `machineError` decoding helper."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Audit RalphCore machine-command subprocess helpers that turn non-zero `runAndCollect` results into user-visible errors, including decomposition, queue recovery, and related machine paths.",
        "Centralize a shared machine-failure decoding path that prefers `MachineErrorDocument` fields over raw stderr while preserving fallback behavior for non-machine failures.",
        "Update `Workspace+Decompose`, queue recovery helpers, and any remaining RalphCore machine command wrappers that still stringify stderr directly to use the shared decoder.",
        "Add or update RalphCore tests so structured `machine_error` stderr surfaces readable code/message/detail/retryable behavior and existing task-conflict classification stays intact.",
