      "id": "RQ-0038",
      "status": "done",
      "title": "Align machine continuation commands with RalphMac surfaces",
      "description": "Versioned machine continuation documents currently embed human-oriented `ralph run ...` commands even when the macOS app consumes those documents and executes only `ralph machine run ...` surfaces. `crates/ralph/src/cli/machine/queue_docs.rs` still emits `ralph run resume` in machine queue repair/undo continuations, and `crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/status.rs` still emits `ralph run loop --parallel <N>` plus `ralph run parallel status --json` in machine-facing continuation next steps. RalphMac formats these machine `next_steps` directly for users in `WorkspaceDiagnosticsService`, while its controller and tests invoke `machine run ...` and `machine run parallel-status`, so the surfaced guidance is not copy-pasteable for Mac operators or automation. Acceptance criteria: machine-facing continuation next steps use `ralph machine ...` equivalents or a dual-field contract that preserves human/machine clarity, the affected CLI tests/docs are updated, and RalphMac fixtures/assertions match the machine surface it actually executes.",
      "priority": "high",
